FBIS4-8989 "dreeu076_i_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-076 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Cease-Fire Agreement Reached in Gorazde Cease-Fire Agreement Reached in Gorazde LD2004003894 Belgrade TANJUG in English 0020 GMT 20 Apr 94 LD2004003894 Belgrade TANJUG English BFN [Text] Sarajevo, April 19 (TANJUG) - Representatives of the Bosnian Serb Republic and the United Nations Protection Force (UNPROFOR) reached a temporary agreement on Gorazde in Pale late on Tuesday [19 April] evening, the Bosnian Serb news agency SRNA reported. "The memorandum on temporary arrangements for Gorazde" calls for an end to combat actions around the town and the deployment of two UNPROFOR platoons with around 100 men. "Serbs agree that they immediately cease all combat activities in an area 3 km from central Gorazde on the left bank of the Drina, unless they are attacked," said the memorandum which was signed by Bosnian Serb Assembly President Momcilo Krajisnik and UNPROFOR Civil administration Head Victor Andreyev.
